@node llabs
@section @code{llabs}---compute the absolute value of an long long integer.
@findex llabs
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <stdlib.h>
long long llabs(long long j);

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
The @code{llabs} function computes the absolute value of the long long integer 
argument @var{j} (also called the magnitude of @var{j}).

The similar function @code{labs} uses and returns @code{long} rather than
@code{long long} values.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
A nonnegative long long integer.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
@code{llabs} is ISO 9899 (C99) compatable.

No supporting OS subroutines are required.

@*
